achet the vineyard holdings are often small averaging at  hectare therefore production sizes are extremely limited yet the domaine commands more than  hectares of grand crus including the entirely faiveley owned corton clos des cortons faiveley grand cru maturation takes place in oak barrels from coopers have been rigorously selected for their fine grain and light toast for red wines a third new oak is used for the premiers crus and two thirds for the grands crus remaining a family run domaine it was françois faiveley who introduced more modern techniques of sorting and fermentation now he has passed this on to his son erwan faiveley who took over the domaine in  and has set about finetuning the winemaking process to make a more gentle elegant style of burgundy the red premiers crus are aged wine produced under the joseph faiveley label are a product of fruit sourced by the negociant arm of the business in many cases from some of the top vineyards in burgundy the faiveley family also own domaine de la framboisiere in mercurey from which they had bought fruit from since  after working together for four generations they bought the domaine in  region burgundy appellation bâtardmontrachet bienvenuebâtardmontrachet bourgogne chambollemusigny corton echézeaux gevreychambertin mazischambertin morey stdenis nuits stgeorges colour range white red number of wines  wines price range £  £ switch to map filter the wine list show   keywords price from to per case ib region alsace argentina  chile armagnac australia austria beaujolais bordeaux burgundy california champagne cognac germany hungary italy justerini  brooks house wines loire madeira mixed case new zealand port rhône s  sw france sherry south africa spain  portugal sparkling wine united kingdom vodka whisky colour white rosé red sweet whisky category cases  bottles bottles only vintages all vintages nv                                                              bottle sizes all bottle sizes l cl cl l l cl cl bottle cl 